bsite=Apple Music AU |date=21 June 2019 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Meditjin\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[JessB]])</span><ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/meditjin-feat-jessb-single/1486982853 |title=Meditjin (feat. JessB) \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=21 November 2019 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Move\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/move-single/1503120711 |title=Move \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=27 March 2020 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 2020\n|-\n|}\n\n====As featured artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Treaty (song)|Treaty '18]]\" <br /><small>([[Yothu Yindi]] & [[67 Special|Gavin Campbell]] featuring Baker Boy)</small>\n| 2018\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!'''Year'''\n!Song\n!Director\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n|\"Cloud 9\" <small>(featuring [[Kian (musician)|Kian]])</small>\n|\n|-\n|\"Marryuna\" <small>(featuring Yirrmal)</small>\n|Daniel King\n|-\n| 2018\n|\"Black Magic\" <small>(featuring [[Dallas Woods]])</small>\n|BraydenFunFilm\n|-\n| 2019\n|\"Cool as Hell\"\n|Gabriel Gasparinatos\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===ARIA Music Awards===\nThe [[ARIA Music Awards]] is an annual award ceremony event celebrating the [[Australian music]] industry. At the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019]], Baker Boy was nominated for three awards.<ref name=\"ARIA noms 2019\">{{cite web | url = https://ariaawards.com.au/news/2019/2019-aria-awards-nominated-artists-revealed | title = ARIA Awards: 2019 ARIA Awards Nominated Artists Revealed | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 10 October 2019 | accessdate = 10 October 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"ARIA noms 2019\">{{cite web | url = https://ariaawards.com.au/news/2019/2019-aria-awards-nominated-artists-revealed | title = ARIA Awards: 2019 ARIA Awards Nominated Artists Revealed | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 10 October 2019 | accessdate = 10 October 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"ARIA 2019 Wins\">{{cite news | url = https://www.ariaawards.com.au/News/2019/2019-ARIA-Award-Winners-Announced | title = 2019 ARIA Award Winners Announced | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 27 November 2019 | accessdate = 5 December 2019 }}</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019|2019]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| \"Cool as Hell\"\n| ARIA Award for Best Hip Hop Release\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ARIA Award for Best Video\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Cool as Hell Tour\n| Best Australian Live Act\n| {{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n===Young Australian of the Year 2019===\nBaker Boy was awarded the 2019 [[List of Young Australian of the Year Award recipients|Young Australian of the Year award]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.australianoftheyear.org.au/2019-award-recipients/|title=Australian of the Year Awards|website=www.australianoftheyear.org.au|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> on the same day as releasing his single \"Cool as Hell\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.australianoftheyear.org.au/2019-award-recipients/|title=Australian of the Year Awards|website=www.australianoftheyear.org.au|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> He delivered his acceptance speech in both English and [[Yolngu Matha]].<ref name=reich>{{cite web | last=Reich | first=Hannah | title=Baker Boy ends his tenure as Young Australian of the Year by taking Yolngu language and dance further into the mainstream| website=ABC News (ABC Arts; Stop Everything!)|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation | date=25 January 2020 | url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-01-25/baker-boy-hip-hop-yolngu-young-australian-of-the-year/11899106 | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Kelly | first=Barb | title=Baker Boy is named 2019 Young Australian of the Year | website=ABC News | date=25 January 2019|format=video | url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-01-25/2019-young-australian/10752208 | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Other awards===\n\nIn August 2018, Baker Boy won two awards at the [[National Indigenous Music Awards]]: Best New Talent and Film Clip of the Year for \"Marryuna\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/nima-2018-winners-announced/|title=2018 National Indigenous Music Award Winners |publisher=NIMA |work=National Indigenous Music Awards |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[National Dreamtime Awards 2018]] Baker was named Male Artist of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aiatsis.gov.au/sites/default/files/docs/digitised_collections/the_koori_mail/m0010050i690r.pdf|title=Dream of love, and success will come (pp32-34)|website=AIATSIS - The Koori Mail|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, Baker Boy was nominated for two awards at the [[National Indigenous Music Awards]]; Winning the Artist of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/national-indigenous-music-awards-unveils-2019-nominations/|title=National Indigenous Music Awards unveils 2019 Nominations |publisher=National Indigenous Music Awards|date=July 2019 |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/record-breaking-crowd-for-the-2019-national-indigenous-music-awards/|title=Record Breaking Crowd for the 2019 National Indigenous Music Awards! |publisher=National Indigenous Music Awards |date=13 August 2019|accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Young Australians of the Year}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Australian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Australian male rappers]]\n[[Category:Indigenous Australian musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Yolngu]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Baker Boy\n| image            = Baker Boy, Laneway Festival 2019.jpg\n| image_size       =\n| landscape        =\n| alt              =\n| caption          = Baker Boy performing at [[St Jerome's Laneway Festival]], 2019\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Danzal Baker\n| native_name      =\n| native_name_lang =\n| alias            =\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1996|10|31}}\n| birth_place      = [[Darwin, Northern Territory]], Australia\n| origin           = [[Milingimbi Island]], [[Arnhem Land]], Northern Territory, Australia\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Australian hip hop]]|[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]|[[Soul music|soul]]}}\n| occupation       = Rapper, dancer, artist, actor\n| instrument       = Vocals, yidaki\n| years_active     = {{startdate|2017}}\u2013present\n| label            =\n| associated_acts  = [[Kian (musician)|Kian]], Dallas Woods, Yirrmal, [[Yothu Yindi]]\n| website          = {{url|https://www.bakerboyofficial.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Danzal Baker''' (born 31 October 1996), known professionally as '''Baker Boy''', is an [[Aboriginal Australian]] rapper, dancer, artist, and actor. A [[Yolngu]] man, Baker Boy is known for performing original [[hip-hop]] songs incorporating both [[English language|English]] and [[Yol\u014bu languages|Yol\u014bu Matha]].\n\nHe was made [[Young Australian of the Year]] in 2019, and his song \"Cool as Hell\" was nominated in several categories in the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019|2019 ARIA Awards]]. In 2018, he won two awards at the [[National Indigenous Music Awards]], and was named Male Artist of the Year in the [[National Dreamtime Awards]].\n\n==Early years==\nBorn in Darwin, Baker Boy grew up in the Arnhem Land communities of [[Milingimbi]] and [[Maningrida, Northern Territory|Maningrida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntnews.com.au/entertainment/arnhem-land-rapper-danzal-baker-making-impact-on-australian-music-scene/news-story/907fbb84e1ba597a4d2c656b87aa9eea |title=Arnhem Land rapper Danzal Baker making impact on Australian music scene |work=NT News |last=Howie |first=Tamara |date=16 July 2017 |accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref> His [[totem]] is the [[Olive Python]], his [[Australian Aboriginal kinship|moiety]] is [[Dhuwa]] and his skin name is Burralung / Gela boy.<ref name=jjj>{{cite web | title=Baker Boy | website=triple j Unearthed | date=2017 | url=https://www.triplejunearthed.com/artist/baker-boy | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nHe studied to [[Year 12]] at Shalom Christian College in [[Townsville, Queensland]], before attending the [[Aboriginal Centre for the Performing Arts]] in [[Brisbane]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/godforbid/2017-05-28/8561738 |title=Baker Boy: Rapping in an Indigenous language |work=Radio National |last=Carleton |first=James |date=28 May 2017 |accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aum.net.au/baker-boy |title=Baker Boy |work=AUM PR + MGMT |accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref> He was able to develop his love of dancing and acting there, and was an original member of the [[Djuki Mala]] dance troupe, which toured Australia.<ref name=jjj/>\n\nIn 2016, Baker appeared on the \"Indigenous\" episode of Australian award-winning series ''[[You Can't Ask That]]'' on [[ABC (Australian TV channel)|ABC TV]].<ref>{{cite web | title=You Can't Ask That|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|format=video | website=ABC iview | date=6 March 2018 | url=https://iview.abc.net.au/show/you-can-t-ask-that/series/1/video/LE1517H008S00 | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=ABC series explores the public perceptions of Indigenous Australia | website=Samaritans | date=6 July 2017 | url=https://www.samaritans.org.au/news_article/abc-series-explores-public-perceptions-indigenous-australia/ | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music career==\n\nIn 2017, Baker Boy attracted national attention as the winner of the [[Triple J Unearthed]] [[National Indigenous Music Awards]] Competition,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/meet-baker-boy-the-deadly-winner-of-our-unearthed-nimas-comp/8702304 |title=Meet Baker Boy, the deadly winner of our Unearthed NIMAs comp |work=Triple J |date=5 July 2017 |accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref> releasing the singles \"Cloud 9\" featuring [[Kian (musician)|Kian]] and \"Marryuna\" featuring Yirrmal in the same year. Both singles were featured in the [[Triple J Hottest 100]] countdown of [[Triple J Hottest 100, 2017|2017]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Baker Boy has two songs crack Triple J Hottest 100 countdown|url=http://www.ntnews.com.au/entertainment/baker-boy-has-two-songs-crack-triple-j-hottest-100-countdown/news-story/bf1f25a6a80ef7a0988c589c50ff00a3|accessdate=29 January 2018|agency=NT News}}</ref>\n\nHe has performed at festivals such as BIGSOUND, [[Groovin' the Moo]] Festival, the [[Woodford Folk Festival]], [[St Jerome's Laneway Festival]], [[WOMADelaide]], and [[Golden Plains Festival]]. In 2018, he performed with acts such as [[Yothu Yindi]] and [[Dizzee Rascal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themusic.com.au/news/all/2017/11/27/laneway-adds-pond,-kirin-j-callinan,-client-liaison,-stella-donnelly,-baker-boy-and-more/ |title=Laneway Adds Pond, Kirin J Callinan, Client Liaison, Stella Donnelly, Baker Boy & More |work=themusic.com.au |date=27 November 2017 |accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"guardian-rising\">{{cite web|last1=Israel|first1=Janine|title=Baker Boy rising: from Arnhem Land to sharing a stage with Dizzee Rascal|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/dec/30/baker-boy-rising-from-arnhem-land-to-sharing-a-stage-with-dizzee-rascal|website=The Guardian|publisher=Guardian News and Media Limited|accessdate=29 January 2018|date=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe performed as an opening act for American rapper [[50 Cent]] in January 2018, along with [[A.B. Original]].<ref name=\"themusic-50cent\">{{cite web|title=AB Original & Baker Boy To Join 50 Cent On His Australian Tour|url=http://themusic.com.au/news/all/2018/01/09/ab-original-and-baker-boy-to-join-50-cent-on-his-australian-tour/|website=The Music|publisher=Street Press Australia Pty Ltd|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"jjj-50cent\">{{cite web|last1=Newstead|first1=Al|title=50 Cent adds A.B. Original and Baker Boy to his Aussie tour|url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/50-cent-adds-ab-original-and-baker-boy-to-his-aussie-tour/9314132|website=Triple J|publisher=ABC|accessdate=29 January 2018|date=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis third single, \"Mr. La Di Da Di\" was released in April 2018. \"Black Magic,\" featuring Dallas Woods, was released in July.\n\nOn 25 January 2019, Baker released his fifth single, \"Cool As Hell.\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Cool as Hell - Single by Baker Boy|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/cool-as-hell-single/1449221282|language=en-us|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> Two days later, \"Mr. La Di Da Di\" was voted into the [[Triple J Hottest 100, 2018|2018 Triple J Hottest 100]].\n\nIn June 2019, Baker released \"In Control\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/in-control-single/1467301485|title=In Control - single|publisher=iTunes Australia|accessdate=22 June 2019}}</ref> On 7 July, Baker Boy appeared on the children's television show, [[Play School (Australian TV series)|Play School]] and performed \"[[Hickory Dickory Dock]]\" as part of [[NAIDOC Week]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pedestrian.tv/music/baker-boy-play-school-celebrity-cover-naidoc-week/|title=Baker Boy Did A Mad As Hell Cover Of \u2018Hickory Dickory Dock\u2019 On \u2018Play School\u2019|publisher=Pedestrian|first=Steffanie|last=Tan|date=8 July 2019|accessdate=2 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nBaker Boy was the headline act at the opening night of the 2019 [[Tarnanthi]] exhibition of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander art at the [[Art Gallery of South Australia]] on 17 October 2019, performing outside the Gallery on [[North Terrace, Adelaide]].<ref>{{cite web|work=The Adelaide Review|url=https://www.adelaidereview.com.au/event-guide/tarnanthi-festival-of-contemporary-aboriginal-torres-strait-islander-art-opening-night/|title=Tarnanthi: Festival of Contemporary Aboriginal And Torres Strait Islander Art + Opening Night|accessdate=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nTwo of his songs made the [[Triple J Hottest 100, 2019|2019 Triple J Hottest 100]]: \"Cloud 9\" at number 76 and \"Marryuna\" at number 17.<ref>{{cite web | title=1-100: Hottest 100 2017 - triple j | website=ABC (Australian Broadcasting Corporation) | date=11 November 2011 | url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/hottest100/17/countdown/1-100/ | access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Newstead | first=Al | title=Baker Boy brings Indigenous language to the Hottest 100 top end | website=triple j | date=28 January 2018 | url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/baker-boy-brings-indigenous-language-to-the-hottest-100-top-end/9367292 | access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nBaker made his debut in ''[[True History of the Kelly Gang (film)|True History of the Kelly Gang]]'', released in cinemas in early January 2019 and on [[Stan (company)|Stan]] from January 26.<ref name=reich/>\n\n==Discography==\n[[File:Baker Boy Dallas Woods Kian 2018 (BB cropped).jpeg|thumb|Baker Boy performing at the [[Riddu Ri\u0111\u0111u]] Festival in [[Norway]], 2018.]]\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Cloud 9\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[Kian (musician)|Kian]])</span><ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/cloud-9-feat-kian-single/1233483277 |title=Cloud 9 (feat. Kian) \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=27 April 2017 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"8\" {{TBA}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://themusicnetwork.com/sotd-baker-boy-brings-the-heat-with-cool-as-hell/ |title=SOTD: Baker Boy brings the heat with 'Cool As Hell' |work=The Music Network |date=29 January 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 |author=Tuskan, Peter}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Marryuna\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring Yirrmal)</span><ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/marryuna-feat-yirrmal-single/1291502168 |title=Marryuna (feat. Yirrmal) \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=6 October 2017 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Mr. La Di Da Di\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/mr-la-di-da-di-single/1364774265 |title=Mr La Di Da Di \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=11 April 2018 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Black Magic\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[Dallas Woods]])</span><ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/black-magic-feat-dallas-woods-single/1406255959 |title=Black Magic (feat. Dallas Woods) \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=13 July 2018 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Cool as Hell\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/cool-as-hell-single/1466569842 |title=Cool as Hell \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=25 January 2019 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"In Control\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/in-control-single/1467301485 |title=In Control \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=21 June 2019 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Meditjin\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[JessB]])</span><ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/meditjin-feat-jessb-single/1486982853 |title=Meditjin (feat. JessB) \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=21 November 2019 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Move\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/move-single/1503120711 |title=Move \u2013 Single by Baker Boy on Apple Music |website=Apple Music AU |date=27 March 2020 |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 2020\n|-\n|}\n\n====As featured artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:13em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Treaty (song)|Treaty '18]]\" <br /><small>([[Yothu Yindi]] & [[67 Special|Gavin Campbell]] featuring Baker Boy)</small>\n| 2018\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!'''Year'''\n!Song\n!Director\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n|\"Cloud 9\" <small>(featuring [[Kian (musician)|Kian]])</small>\n|\n|-\n|\"Marryuna\" <small>(featuring Yirrmal)</small>\n|Daniel King\n|-\n| 2018\n|\"Black Magic\" <small>(featuring [[Dallas Woods]])</small>\n|BraydenFunFilm\n|-\n| 2019\n|\"Cool as Hell\"\n|Gabriel Gasparinatos\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===ARIA Music Awards===\nThe [[ARIA Music Awards]] is an annual award ceremony event celebrating the [[Australian music]] industry. At the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019]], Baker Boy was nominated for three awards.<ref name=\"ARIA noms 2019\">{{cite web | url = https://ariaawards.com.au/news/2019/2019-aria-awards-nominated-artists-revealed | title = ARIA Awards: 2019 ARIA Awards Nominated Artists Revealed | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 10 October 2019 | accessdate = 10 October 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"ARIA noms 2019\">{{cite web | url = https://ariaawards.com.au/news/2019/2019-aria-awards-nominated-artists-revealed | title = ARIA Awards: 2019 ARIA Awards Nominated Artists Revealed | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 10 October 2019 | accessdate = 10 October 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"ARIA 2019 Wins\">{{cite news | url = https://www.ariaawards.com.au/News/2019/2019-ARIA-Award-Winners-Announced | title = 2019 ARIA Award Winners Announced | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | date = 27 November 2019 | accessdate = 5 December 2019 }}</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[ARIA Music Awards of 2019|2019]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| \"Cool as Hell\"\n| ARIA Award for Best Hip Hop Release\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ARIA Award for Best Video\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Cool as Hell Tour\n| Best Australian Live Act\n| {{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n===Young Australian of the Year 2019===\nBaker Boy was awarded the 2019 [[List of Young Australian of the Year Award recipients|Young Australian of the Year award]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.australianoftheyear.org.au/2019-award-recipients/|title=Australian of the Year Awards|website=www.australianoftheyear.org.au|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> on the same day as releasing his single \"Cool as Hell\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.australianoftheyear.org.au/2019-award-recipients/|title=Australian of the Year Awards|website=www.australianoftheyear.org.au|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref> He delivered his acceptance speech in both English and [[Yolngu Matha]].<ref name=reich>{{cite web | last=Reich | first=Hannah | title=Baker Boy ends his tenure as Young Australian of the Year by taking Yolngu language and dance further into the mainstream| website=ABC News (ABC Arts; Stop Everything!)|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation | date=25 January 2020 | url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-01-25/baker-boy-hip-hop-yolngu-young-australian-of-the-year/11899106 | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Kelly | first=Barb | title=Baker Boy is named 2019 Young Australian of the Year | website=ABC News | date=25 January 2019|format=video | url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-01-25/2019-young-australian/10752208 | access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Other awards===\n\nIn August 2018, Baker Boy won two awards at the [[National Indigenous Music Awards]]: Best New Talent and Film Clip of the Year for \"Marryuna\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/nima-2018-winners-announced/|title=2018 National Indigenous Music Award Winners |publisher=NIMA |work=National Indigenous Music Awards |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[National Dreamtime Awards 2018]] Baker was named Male Artist of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://aiatsis.gov.au/sites/default/files/docs/digitised_collections/the_koori_mail/m0010050i690r.pdf|title=Dream of love, and success will come (pp32-34)|website=AIATSIS - The Koori Mail|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, Baker Boy was nominated for two awards at the [[National Indigenous Music Awards]]; Winning the Artist of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/national-indigenous-music-awards-unveils-2019-nominations/|title=National Indigenous Music Awards unveils 2019 Nominations |publisher=National Indigenous Music Awards|date=July 2019 |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nima.musicnt.com.au/news/record-breaking-crowd-for-the-2019-national-indigenous-music-awards/|title=Record Breaking Crowd for the 2019 National Indigenous Music Awards! |publisher=National Indigenous Music Awards |date=13 August 2019|accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Young Australians of the Year}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Australian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Australian male rappers]]\n[[Category:Indigenous Australian musicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\