{"title_page": "Dermatopolymyositis", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Dermatopolymyositis\n| synonyms        =  '''PM/DM'''<ref name=\"pmid9921402\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Chraibi S, Ibnabdeljalil H, Habbal R, Bennis A, Tahiri A, Chraibi N |title=Pericardial tamponade as the first manifestation of dermatopolymyositis |journal=Ann Med Interne (Paris) |volume=149 |issue=7 |pages=464\u20136 |date=November 1998 |pmid=9921402 |doi= |url=}}</ref>\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Dermatopolymyositis'''  is a family of [[myositis]] disorders that includes [[polymyositis]] and [[dermatomyositis]]. As such, it includes both a distinctive skin rash and progressive muscular weakness. <ref name=\"pmid4093921\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Tymms KE, Webb J |title=Dermatopolymyositis and other connective tissue diseases: a review of 105 cases |journal=J. Rheumatol. |volume=12 |issue=6 |pages=1140\u20138 |date=December 1985 |pmid=4093921 |doi= |url=}}</ref> It is a rare disease.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = \n| ICD10           = {{ICD10|M|33|90}} - {{ICD10|M|33|99}}\n| ICD9            = {{ICD9|710.3}}\n| ICDO            = \n| OMIM            = \n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = \n| eMedicineTopic  = \n| MeshID          = D003882\n| ICD10CM         = {{ICD10CM|M33}}\n}}\n{{Systemic connective tissue disorders}}\n\n[[Category:Inflammations]]\n[[Category:Systemic connective tissue disorders]]\n\n\n{{musculoskeletal-disease-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical condition (new)\n| name            = Dermatopolymyositis\n| synonyms        =  '''PM/DM'''<ref name=\"pmid9921402\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Chraibi S, Ibnabdeljalil H, Habbal R, Bennis A, Tahiri A, Chraibi N |title=Pericardial tamponade as the first manifestation of dermatopolymyositis |journal=Ann Med Interne (Paris) |volume=149 |issue=7 |pages=464\u20136 |date=November 1998 |pmid=9921402 |doi= |url=}}</ref>\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| pronounce       = \n| field           = \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Dermatopolymyositis'''  is a family of [[myositis]] disorders that includes [[polymyositis]] and [[dermatomyositis]]. As such, it includes both a distinctive skin rash and progressive muscular weakness. <ref name=\"pmid4093921\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Tymms KE, Webb J |title=Dermatopolymyositis and other connective tissue diseases: a review of 105 cases |journal=J. Rheumatol. |volume=12 |issue=6 |pages=1140\u20138 |date=December 1985 |pmid=4093921 |doi= |url=}}</ref> It is a rare disease.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|  DiseasesDB     =  \n|  ICD10          = {{ICD10|M|33|90}} - {{ICD10|M|33|99}}\n|  ICD9           = {{ICD9|710.3}} \n|  ICDO           =  \n|  OMIM           =  \n|  MedlinePlus    =  \n|  eMedicineSubj  =  \n|  eMedicineTopic =  \n|  MeshID         = D003882\n}}\n{{Systemic connective tissue disorders}}\n\n[[Category:Inflammations]]\n[[Category:Systemic connective tissue disorders]]\n\n\n{{musculoskeletal-disease-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Dismanet", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding new medical resources.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatopolymyositis"}
